The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, January 28, 2004 				 ONGC filing today
																								New Delhi, Jan. 27 (PTI): ONGC today made last-minute changes in the draft red herring prospectus for the public issue of 10 per cent shares of the government. The preliminary offer document could be filed with Sebi on Wednesday. Board members fine-tuned certain risks and management view of the business to incorporate views of the petroleum ministry, which delayed the filing. 																								The prospectus will, in all probability, be filed tomorrow, a senior company official said.																								In all, 14.2 crore equity shares will be sold to retail investors in lots of 10. Of the total stocks, 10 per cent has been reserved for the employees of the company and subsidiary firms like MRPL and ONGC Videsh Limited. 																								Of the remaining shares, 50 per cent will go to qualified institutional buyers; 25 per cent each will be reserved for retail investors and high net-worth individuals. 
